  "title": "Senior IT Infrastructure Specialist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Purpose:</strong> The Senior IT Infrastructure Specialist will serve as the primary technical lead for desktop and end-user infrastructure within the <strong>Banking and Financial Services (BFS)</strong>\nenvironment. You will be the single point of contact for rapid service\nrestoration while proactively managing a diverse fleet of Windows and macOS\ndevices.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Tier2.5 Infrastructure Support:</strong> Provide advanced troubleshooting for complex user issues, triaging incidents across infrastructure, database, and application layers.</li><li><strong>Hybrid Device Management:</strong> Manage and maintain the Desktop Standard Operating Environment (SOE) for both <strong>Windows and macOS</strong> fleets using enterprise-grade MDM solutions.</li><li><strong>Proactive System Monitoring:</strong> Perform daily proactive health checks of the infrastructure and 40+ core business applications to prevent downtime.</li><li><strong>Migration & Project Leadership:</strong> Lead and support critical IT projects, including large-scale OS migrations (e.g., Windows 10/11) and hardware refresh cycles.</li><li><strong>UAM & Compliance:</strong> Manage User Access Management (UAM) and ensure all support activities align with <strong>ITIL V3/V4</strong> frameworks and strict banking regulatory standards.</li></ul><p><strong>Technical Skills & Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>MDM Expertise: </strong>Proven experience in managing application deployments and device policies via <strong>JAMF (macOS)</strong> and <strong>Microsoft Intune (Windows/Mobile)</strong>.</li><li><strong>Advanced Monitoring Tools:</strong> High proficiency in enterprise monitoring suites such as <strong>ITRS Geneos</strong> and job scheduling tools like <strong>Autosys </strong>for batch monitoring.</li><li><strong>Scripting & Automation:</strong> Ability to automate routine health checks and deployments using <strong>Shell Scripting, PowerShell, and YAML (Ansible)</strong>.</li><li><strong>Middleware Knowledge:</strong> Basic administration and troubleshooting of middleware platforms,\n     specifically <strong>IBM WebSphere</strong> and <strong>Apache Tomcat</strong>.</li><li><strong>Domain Knowledge:</strong> 10+ years of experience in a Production Support or Deskside Support role\n     within the <strong>Banking/Finance sector</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Education:</strong> Bachelor’s  Degree in Information Technology or a related field.</li><li><strong>Certification:</strong> <strong>ITIL Foundation Certification</strong> is mandatory.</li></ul><p><strong>Platform Experience:</strong></p><p> Strong familiarity with multi-OS environments (Linux, Windows, macOS)</p>",
